This paper discusses the evaluation of automatic question generation systems, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of metrics for evaluating the performance of these systems, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of knowledge graphs and documents, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper proposes a new scoring function, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
